19/02/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- NATO has maintained and extended its efforts to achieve security, stability and prosperity among its members and in regions adjacent to the Euro-Atlantic zone, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Wednesday (18 February). In a speech marking the 52nd anniversary of membership in the Alliance, he said Turkey is now more than ever working within the structure to face 21st century threats such as terrorism and the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.
In other news, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul begins an official two-day visit to Russia on Monday, the first visit at this level in eight years. He will meet with President Vladimir Putin, among others. (Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 18/02/04)
